answers.body_markdown:
Instead of creating new vertex array data for each character, use the same data for all characters. Add a model matrix to the shader code:

```glsl
in vec2 vertexCoord;

uniform mat4 projMatrix;
uniform mat4 modelMatrix;

void main()
{
    // [...]  

    gl_Position = projMatrix * modelMatrix * vec4(vertexCoord.xy, 0.0, 1.0);
}
```

For each character a rectangle from (0, 0) to (1, 1) is draw. Setup a model matrix for each glyph, which

- scales the character to its size

  ```cpp
  GLfloat   w      = ch.Size.x * scale;
  GLfloat   h      = ch.Size.y * scale;
  glm::mat4 scaleM = glm::scale(glm::mat4(1.0f), glm::vec3(w, h, 1.0f));
  ``` 

- moves the character to the position in the text (`char_x` is incremented for each character)

  ```cpp
  GLfloat   xrel      = char_x + ch.Bearing.x * scale;
  GLfloat   yrel      = (ch.Size.y - ch.Bearing.y) * scale;
  glm::mat4 transRelM = glm::translate(glm::mat4(1.0f), glm::vec3(xrel, yrel, 0.0f));
  ```

- rotates the text

  ```cpp
